===Glyph origin===
{{Han etym}}
In oracle bone script, {{Han compound|дҮӮ|жңҲ|ls=psc|ls2=ic|c2=p|t1=sickle|t2=moon}}. The original meaning was likely "to work (with a sickle) under the moonlight".

In bronze inscriptions the character corrupted into the modern form {{Han compound|ls=psc|иү№|иҫҘ|c2=p|c1=s|t1=grass}}.

